mechanics, laboratory, animal care, administration and many other service professions, they experience first-hand the fascination of research - often in a project-oriented manner and in an international environment. The Max Planck Society offers about 30 different apprenticeships to support scientists. A good 80 percent of the 86 Max Planck Institutes and also headquarters are involved in vocational training. Equal Opportunities Talent, creativity and passion - that's what the Max Planck Society relies on. It supports all employees equally. Because research needs diversity. This is also formulated in the Code of Conduct, the core values of the Max Planck Society: "We treat each other with respect and do not tolerate any form of discrimination based on ethnicity, gender, disability, religion or belief, age, sexual orientation or identity." With that, the Code of Conduct identifies the nine key areas that comprise the understanding of diversity. An open, international, diverse and inclusive work culture lays the foundation for the cutting-edge research conducted at the 86 Max Planck Institutes. [more] Living in T√ºbingen People from more than 140 nations live in T√ºbingen. Tolerance is very important to the residents. The city has an environmentally conscious image and many people feel connected to nature. Modern young neighborhoods such as the French Quarter have been awarded the German and European City Prizes. [more] Information for Schools Since 2005, the Max Planck Society has been offering the latest information, images and video clips on current and much-discussed research topics such as stem cells, climate change, black holes and fuel cells. The max-wissen portal is aimed particularly at all those who want to keep up to date or go deeper than conventional textbooks allow. [more] Job Offers Here you find vacant positions at the Max Planck Campus T√ºbingen. [more] Information for Students The support of young scientists is an important goal at the Max Planck Campus T√ºbingen. Our internationally leading PhD programs aim to train the future generation of first-class scientists. The programs offer you the opportunity to work at the top of your field and are an excellent platform for a successful career in science. [more] Research Location T√ºbingen The university town of T√ºbingen is just 20 minutes from Stuttgart Airport. T√ºbingen offers a lively center with medieval flair and a rich cultural and arts offering: readings, concerts, international film festivals and markets ensure that life here is never boring. [more] More information Career paths Information about individual career planning at the Max Planck Society. more Top Information for Media Students Schools Self Service Max-Planck-Gesellschaft Imprint Privacy Policy ¬© 2024, Max-Planck-Gesellschaft ¬© 2003-2024, Max-Planck-Gesellschaft Web-View Print Page Open in new window Estimated DIN-A4 page-width Go to Editor View	{scientists,biology,universities,science,university,laboratory,cybernetics,laboratories,t√ºbingen,textbooks,newsroom,concerts,students,class,stuttgart,research,scholars,apprentices,festivals,degrees,apprenticeships,technology,future,bachelor,europe,campus,max,talent,passion,wealth,degree,european,mechanics,friedrich,schools,web,prizes,film,institutes,workshops,creativity,job,employees,career,date,opportunities,media,goal,society,gender,arts,diversity,award,french,electronics,nations,miescher,city,editor,neighborhoods,professions,religion}	2024-07-14 16:10:03.437179	{https://www.tuebingen.mpg.de/en,https://www.tuebingen.mpg.de/karriere,https://www.tuebingen.mpg.de/84646/max-planck-institut-fuer-biologische-kybernetik,https://www.tuebingen.mpg.de/84448/mpi-fuer-biologie-tuebingen,https://www.tuebingen.mpg.de/84502/mpi-fuer-intelligente-systeme,https://www.tuebingen.mpg.de/84532/friedrich-miescher-labor,https://www.tuebingen.mpg.de/84433/zentrale-einrichtungen,https://www.tuebingen.mpg.de/184582/newsroom,https://www.tuebingen.mpg.de/185915/alle_Veranstalt