 the European Union, and are not disqualified from voting in the Federal Republic of Germany or in their member state of origin. Legal basis Section 6 (3) of the European Elections Act (EuWG) Back to top How can I take part in the election in Germany? A Union citizen who wants to go to the polls in Germany has to be on the voters‚Äô register. Registration ex officio Union citizens entitled to vote will ex officio be entered in a voters‚Äô register by the competent municipal authority if they were enrolled in a voters‚Äô register in the Federal Republic of Germany for the European Parliament election of 13 June 1999 or a later European election, provided they are registered with a residents‚Äô registration office on the 42 nd day before the election (= 28 April 2024) and had not departed to a foreign country in the meantime. Like all others entitled to vote, they will receive a voter‚Äôs notification from the municipal authority by the 21 st day before the election at the latest. Union citizens who moved abroad and returned to the Federal Republic of Germany have to re-apply for entry in a voters‚Äô register. Registration upon application Union citizens who are not entered ex officio into a voters‚Äô register (see no. 1.) have to submit a formal application to be registered. The application must have been received by the municipality of their place of residence on the 21 st day before election (= 19 May 2024) at the latest. This period cannot be extended. The application has to bear the applicant‚Äôs personal handwritten signature; its original must be submitted to the competent municipal authority. The application must not be sent by e-mail or fax. You may download the application form from this webpage as pdf file. It contains an information leaflet with instructions for completing the form. Printed application forms are available in the electoral office of your municipality. Application form: Antrag f√ºr Unionsb√ºrgerinnen und Unionsb√ºrger auf Eintragung in das W